{
  "texts": [
    "Zhu et al. [36] proposed ECFNet to effectively restore UDC images which takes multi-scale images as input.",
    "Net [27] is a novel architecture that learns a rich set of features incorporating contextual information from multiple scales while maintaining high resolution.After the Transformer model shined in the field of natural language processing, Vision Transformer (ViT) [5] has also been extensively explored in high-level visual tasks, such as object detection [1,35], image segmentation [24,33], etc.",
    "Transformer has the ability to capture long-range dependencies between image patches and adapt to given input content.",
    "Due to these characteristics, Transformer is also used in the field of image restoration [12,21,34].",
    "Shuf-fleFormer [23] proposes a local window Transformer based on a random shuffling strategy to model non-local interactions with linear complexity."
  ]
}